Search for a specific pattern in a file with grep:
- grep -n 'Name to be searched' <specific file or folder / * for all >
Create New Directory:
- mkdir <dir name>
Recursively remove a directory:
- rm -r <dir name>
Recursively copy the content of one file to a second file
- cp -r <source folder name> <target folder name>
Archive existing file
- zip <zip filename> <name of the folder to be zipped>
Unarchive an existing archive file.
- unzip <zipped file name>
Give read, write, and execute permission to owner, and read and execute permission to group and others:
- chmod 755 <folder path>
Change the ownership of a file:
- chown <username> <folder path>
